# Monetization_Design

## 1. Applies when
Games with in-app purchases, premium currency, battle passes, subscriptions,
loot boxes, or ad-based revenue.

## 2. This document owns
Monetization strategy and revenue model design; premium currency systems and
exchange rates; battle pass structure, tiers, and reward pacing; loot box mechanics,
drop rates, and pity timers; subscription tiers and benefits; ad placement, frequency,
and rewarded ad design; store layout, pricing tiers, and bundle offers; regional
pricing and platform fee accounting; spending limits, parental controls, and
responsible monetization.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Core gameplay loop (Gameplay_Systems); progression system (Progression_Design);
LiveOps event scheduling (LiveOps_Design); UI layout of store screens
(UI_UX_Design); legal compliance for gambling regulations (separate legal review).

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Revenue Model & Strategy · 2. Premium Currency · 3. Battle Pass ·
4. Loot Boxes & Gacha · 5. Subscriptions · 6. Advertising · 7. Store & Pricing ·
8. Responsible Monetization

## 5. Common boundaries
- Monetization vs Gameplay — "how revenue is generated" vs "what the player does".
- Premium currency exchange rates live here; what currency buys lives in
  Resource_And_Economy.
- Battle pass reward pacing lives here; progression XP curves live in
  Progression_Design.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Revenue model must reference enabled game systems.
- Loot box drop rates must be documented and auditable.
- Responsible monetization must reference platform requirements.
